                    h2 Art direction
                    p A red-orange hue and its shade, along with a tint and a shade of grey makes up this monochromatic color palette. The vibrant red-orange emphasizes certain parts of the design without being as overpowering as red. It is chosen for its strong association with creativity.
                    p The display font is GT Walsheim in a medium weight. The typeface has a symmetrical design and when used in a condensed style, creates rectangular shapes that is coherent with the shapes used in the design. GT Flexa Mono is naturally condensed and quite bold at a regular weight, which makes it legible and also why it is chosen.
                div#color-wrapper
                    div#biennale-primary.color 
                    div#biennale-secondary.color 
                    div#biennale-white.color 
                    div#biennale-black.color 
                p.caption Monochromatic Color Palette

                img(src="../img/biennale-typography.png", alt="Typography")
                p.caption Typography

                div
                    h2 Design process
                    p We started by studying Ellen Lupton’s design principles and Chris Ashworth’s design qualities. We chose two principles and three qualities, and grouped images that matched the principles and qualities. This would give us a better idea of how to apply them in our design process.
                
                div.list-wrapper 
                    h2 Design principles 
                    ul
                        li 1. Creating spatial planes with graphic transparency
                        li 2. Misaligning text to break structure  

                    h2 Design qualities 
                    ul 
                        li 1. Overlapping elements to develop narratives
                        li 2. Off-grid arrangement for visual weight
                        li 3. Placement of shapes to create tension

                img(src="../img/image-grouping.png", alt="Picture of Image Grouping")
                p.caption Final image grouping according to principle and quality

                p We developed 3 lines of investigation by combining one principle with one quality. We then designed multiple posters for each line, experimenting with different typefaces, color, and image treatment.

                div.list-wrapper 
                    h2 3 Lines of investigation
                    ul
                        li 1. Placement of shapes and misaligned text
                        li 2. Off-grid arrangement and misaligned text
                        li 3. Overlapping elements & misaligned text
                
